As far as i know private key length of 2048 is better than 4096, is there any specific reason why were are choosing 4096 for this purpose?

https://expeditedsecurity.com/blog/measuring-ssl-rsa-keys/

above link states why lot of websites like github still use 2048 ,even when 4096 gives better encryption.The RSA signs per second varies drastically when we switch over to 4096.

4096 is max length of CSR string.
we did not find any instance of csr string crossing 4k even with 2048 or 4096.
we can explore more on this
